7. SOURCE CODE ESCROW

The Licensor shall deposit the source code of the Licensed Work with a reputable third-party escrow agent under a formal escrow agreement prior to or concurrently with entering into the first Commercial License agreement.

All customers who have entered into a valid Commercial License agreement with the Licensor shall be named as beneficiaries of the escrow arrangement as a standard term of such Commercial License.

The Licensor shall update the escrow deposit promptly following each material release of the Licensed Work to ensure that the deposited source code remains current.

The escrow agreement shall provide for release of the source code to beneficiaries upon the occurrence of defined release conditions, including:

(a) Insolvency of the Licensor; or
(b) Permanent cessation of trading by the Licensor.

Upon release, beneficiaries shall receive sufficient rights to use, modify, and maintain the released source code solely as necessary to continue operating the Licensed Work for their own business purposes, including through third-party contractors acting on their behalf.

The terms and operation of the escrow arrangement shall be governed by a separate escrow agreement with the escrow agent, provided that such terms shall not materially diminish the protections described in this Section.

